dev/plans/0.6.0-Phase-9-Pack-5-performance-diagnostics.md:582:- 2026-05-03 A.1 KEEP `ca0d8f0` — perf record + flamegraphs N=5 per sub-phase. Phase JSON decision INCONCLUSIVE per A.1 mandate (capture-only); orchestrator KEEP because all acceptance criteria met. seq median 182ms (stddev 9.2), conc median 115ms (stddev 4.0), speedup 1.58× vs required 5.33×. Concurrent profile dominated by aarch64 atomics + `___pthread_mutex_lock` (~30% cycles vs ~5% sequential). Independent secondary: `sqlite3RunParser` 4-5% both profiles. Artifacts in `dev/notes/perf/ac020-*-fec71a0.{svg,folded}` and `dev/plans/runs/A1-folded-diff.txt`. Raw `perf.data` (10.3 MB) excluded — regenerable. CPU governor stayed `schedutil` (no sudo); perf 5.15.163 vs kernel 5.15.185-tegra. Worktree cleaned.
dev/plans/0.6.0-Phase-9-Pack-5-performance-diagnostics.md:590:- 2026-05-03 E.1 REVERT (via `git revert` `1739b17`+`3e047a3`; original commits `e4ff255`+`91c69e9` archived). Implementation correct: 4 read-path stmts (`vec0_match`/`canonical_lookup`/`soft_fallback_probe`/`fts_match`) on `prepare_cached`, prepares per search drop 4→0 post-warmup. **Sequential -13.7%** (182→157 ms; parse-cost relief real). **Concurrent unchanged** (115→125 ms; +3.5 ms vs B.1/C.1 drift baseline; flat). Speedup 1.58→1.266× (-19.9%; lower seq tightens AC-020 bound, gate worsens). AC-017 + AC-018 green. Codex `gpt-5.4` reviewer **BLOCK** with three findings: (1) new `pub fn _for_test` accessors expand public surface without ADR/rust.md update; (2) `conc_median=125 > 115` matches written REVERT rule, not committed INCONCLUSIVE; (3) test exercised 3/4 stmts (300 not 400 baseline misses). Phase 7/8 invariants PASS. Pivot: residual conc contention is upstream of parse cost — most likely rusqlite-side Mutex or our `ReaderPool::borrow` Mutex<Vec<Connection>>; less likely WAL shared-memory atomics. All three are architectural (lock-free pool replacement / structural SQLite usage change), out of Pack 5 scope. Skipping E.3 (§5 already noted cache_size doesn't change conc ratio) and E.4 (writer-side, workload is read-heavy). Mutex + parse tracks both exhausted ⇒ Pack 5 final synthesis next.
dev/plans/0.6.0-Phase-9-Pack-5-performance-diagnostics.md:593:- 2026-05-04 Pack 6.G G.1 LANDED INCONCLUSIVE (cherry-pick `b0aceca` + comment fix `5960741`) — `sqlite3_db_config(SQLITE_DBCONFIG_LOOKASIDE,NULL,1200,500)` per F.0 reader worker. Conc 168→161 ms (−7 ms / 0.41 stddev), speedup 3.339→3.530× (+0.191×, no ratio worsening). Misses formal KEEP threshold by 4.89 ms; codex CONCERN with RUN_MORE_VERIFICATION. Landed regardless on canonical-best-practice + topology argument. Lookaside hiwtr=57/500 slots/worker — config provably honored. Output `dev/plans/runs/G1-reader-lookaside-output.json`; review `dev/plans/runs/G1-review-20260504T141437Z.md`.
