dev/plans/runs/G1-review-20260504T141139Z.md:1677:"decision_self": "INCONCLUSIVE",
dev/plans/runs/G1-review-20260504T141139Z.md:1678:"decision_self_rationale": "AC-017 + AC-018 stayed green. Concurrent_median improved 168 ms -> 161 ms (-7 ms, ~4.2%) and speedup_median improved 3.339x -> 3.530x (+0.191x, no ratio worsening). Per handoff §6 / §8 the KEEP threshold is `concurrent_median < baseline - 1*stddev` = 168 - 11.89 = 156.11 ms; observed 161 ms misses the threshold by 4.89 ms (less than half a stddev). Movement is in the right direction but inside the noise band, so the implementer self-decision is INCONCLUSIVE. Lookaside-applied evidence captured below for the orchestrator + codex `gpt-5.4` high reviewer to confirm KEEP-or-REVERT.",
dev/plans/runs/G1-review-20260504T141139Z.md:1767:"optional_sweep_notes": "Did not run the [128, 250, 500, 1000] x {512, 1200} sweep grid. Spec §2 makes it optional ('do NOT bake the sweep into the production code path'); G.0 telemetry already pointed at 1200 x 500 as the right canonical sizing for the sticky reader topology and the small-allocation footprint of the FTS5 / vec0 hot stacks. If the orchestrator + reviewer want the sweep before deciding KEEP vs INCONCLUSIVE, it can be done as a follow-up under a debug-gated env knob without re-opening the public surface; the lookaside-call helper is already isolated in `configure_reader_lookaside`.",
dev/plans/runs/G1-review-20260504T141139Z.md:1804:"for_orchestrator": "Codex `gpt-5.4` high reviewer mandatory on this INCONCLUSIVE per handoff §7. If the reviewer + orchestrator KEEP, pivot to G.4 (private page cache) — that lever attacks the second-largest G.0 contention class (`page_cache` 6.29% conc with 4.01x ratio) and is canonical-SQLite (`SQLITE_OPEN_PRIVATECACHE` / `PRAGMA cache=private`), distinct from the §3 do-not-retry `cache_size` global tuning entry. If the reviewer REVERTS, the same G.4 candidate becomes the next phase since the residual is then NOT allocator-arena.",
dev/plans/runs/G1-review-20260504T141139Z.md:1810:The phase prompt and output JSON are consistent on the intended decision rule: this is an INCONCLUSIVE candidate unless the reviewer finds a contract or process violation. I still need the memory/feedback files and the actual diff/log evidence for TDD, verify usage, and invariant preservation.
