er A.4 OVERRIDE update 2026-05-03.\",\n \"decision_rule_met\": false,\n \"decision_rule_evaluation\": \"concurrent_median = 120.6 ms > 115 ms threshold (REVERT trigger). Speedup 1.526x is essentially unchanged from A.1 baseline 1.58x (within 1 stddev: stddev_speedup=0.025). Sequential effectively unchanged (+1.1%). Concurrent shifted +4.9% which is ~1.7 stddev — borderline but on the wrong side of the gate. Strict rule: REVERT.\",\n \"kill_criteria_met\": false,\n \"kill_criteria_note\": \"Kill rule (B.1 + B.3 stacked < 10% drop ⇒ promote D.1) requires B.3 also to land. B.1 alone shows 0% drop (mild regression within noise). Ready to evaluate after B.3 or in light of C.1 hypothesis below.\",\n \"reviewer_verdict\": \"PENDING\",\n \"reviewer_concerns\": [],\n \"reviewer_log\": \"dev/plans/runs/B1-review-<ts>.md (orchestrator to run)\",\n \"phase78_review_verdict\": \"PENDING\",\n \"phase78_review_log\": \"dev/plans/runs/B1-review-phase78-<ts>.md (orchestrator to run)\",\n \"loc_added\": 119,\n \"loc_removed\": 0,\n \"files_changed_pre_revert\": [\n \"src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/src/lib.rs\",\n \"src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/tests/multithread_wiring.rs\"\n ],\n \"files_changed\": [],\n \"commit_sha\": \"none\",\n \"git_status_clean_after_revert\": true,\n \"data_for_pivot\": \"APPLIED-BUT-DIDN'T-HELP. sqlite3_config(SQLITE_CONFIG_MULTITHREAD) was correctly invoked at open_locked head BEFORE any Connection::open; rc=SQLITE_OK=0 (vs §5's silent 21). init_sqlite_runtime is OnceLock-cached (idempotent across reopens). Yet the AC-020 ratio is unchanged (1.526x vs A.1 1.58x; concurrent 120.6 vs 115 ms — within noise). Interpretation: runtime threading-mode downgrade from SERIALIZED (compile-pinned 1) to MULTITHREAD does NOT relieve the bottleneck. Two explanations consistent with the A.1 hot-symbol set (**aarch64_swp4_rel/\_cas4_acq dominant in concurrent): (a) per-connection mutex elimination requires compile-time SQLITE_THREADSAFE=2 + SQLITE_NO_MUTEX, not runtime config — promotes C.1 to next; (b) the contended primitive is the WAL-pager spinlock which is unaffected by threading-mode flag — promotes D.1 (per-conn lookaside or different reader architecture). Recommend running C.1 first (cheaper to test the hypothesis: rebuild libsqlite3-sys with -DSQLITE_THREADSAFE=2 and re-measure). If C.1 still shows no improvement, kill the mutex track and pivot to D.1.\",\n \"unexpected_observations\": \"The 5 runs were tightly clustered (concurrent stddev 2.98 ms) with no outliers; AC-018 stayed green; AC-017 stayed green. The B.1 intervention is provably wired (config_rc=0 cached in OnceLock, idempotent across reopens), eliminating the §5-class silent-no-op failure mode. The fact that wiring works but perf is flat is itself a high-confidence signal that the runtime threading-mode flag is NOT the right knob — the dominant SQLite primitives we observed in A.1 (**aarch64_swp4_rel, **aarch64*cas4_acq, ***pthread*mutex_lock) are not the SQLite global-mutex which CONFIG_MULTITHREAD relaxes; they are likely WAL-pager spinlocks and per-connection mutexes that only SQLITE_THREADSAFE=2 (compile-time, C.1 territory) can disable. Pre-existing compile errors in tests/{compatibility,cursors,lifecycle_observability}.rs are A.0 baseline (noted in A.1 pre_flight_notes); not B.1's regression.\",\n \"next_phase_recommendation\": \"C1\",\n \"next_phase_recommendation_rationale\": \"B.1 ruled out the runtime threading-mode hypothesis with a clean, observable gate (config_rc=0 yet ratio flat). Two surviving hypotheses: C.1 (compile-time SQLITE_THREADSAFE=2 / SQLITE_NO_MUTEX rebuild — directly addresses the per-connection mutex symbols dominating the concurrent flame) and D.1 (architectural — per-conn lookaside or alt reader topology). C.1 is a smaller-radius intervention and tests a more specific hypothesis with the same evidence stack; recommend C.1 first. If C.1 also lands flat, kill the mutex track per the A.4 kill criterion and promote D.1.\",\n \"tests_run_summary\": {\n \"lib_tests\": \"1 passed\",\n \"multithread_wiring\": \"2 passed (init_sqlite_runtime_runs_on_engine_open_and_captures_sqlite_ok, init_sqlite_runtime_is_idempotent_across_engine_reopens)\",\n \"perf_gates\": \"AC-017 green, AC-018 green, AC-020 long-run failed (expected — perf gate not met)\",\n \"lifecycle_reliability\": \"4 passed, 3 ignored (AC-021/022a green)\",\n \"vector_contracts\": \"7 passed\",\n \"projection_runtime\": \"12 passed, 1 ignored\",\n \"op_store\": \"7 passed\",\n \"error_taxonomy\": \"12 passed\",\n \"instrumentation_methods\": \"5 passed\",\n \"cursor_read_after_write\": \"1 passed\",\n \"search_result_shape\": \"2 passed\",\n \"property_template\": \"1 passed\",\n \"compile_errors_pre_existing\": [\"tests/compatibility.rs\", \"tests/cursors.rs\", \"tests/lifecycle_observability.rs (test file with compile errors at lines 414/446/453/489)\"],\n \"compile_errors_pre_existing_note\": \"A.0/A.1 baseline; documented in dev/plans/runs/A1-perf-capture-output.json pre_flight_notes.build_note. Not introduced by B.1.\"\n }\n}\n","numLines":89,"startLine":1,"totalLines":89}}}
